org.safs.cukes.steps

Class StepDefinitions

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.safs.cukes.steps.StepDefinitions

  • public class StepDefinitions
extends java.lang.Object
    The included runDriverCommand and runComponentFunction methods serve as valid Cukes Steps using the @Then annotation. So, they can be invoked automatically by a running Cukes test if the feature file uses the appropriate Step syntax to match one of these Step Definitions.

    They can also be called explicitly from other custom step definition implementations.

    Author:
    Carl Nagle
    See Also:
    JSAFSDriver

    • Method Detail

      • beforeAll

        public void beforeAll()
        Must be called by Cukes at least once to initialize the JSAFSDriver.

        It can be called automatically by the execution of Scenarios, or be called from an overriding test controller like a JUnit runner, if appropriate.

        If the steps in this class match any steps in the executing Scenario, then this method will automatically be called. If not, then a @JSAFSBefore step from another step definition file for the executing Scenario(s) can invoke this method.

        Example: 

        
  public class OtherStepdefs {

      @JSAFSBefore(order=10)
      public void beforeAll(){
          StepDriver.beforeAll();
      }
      ...
 }

        @Then(value="do safs command ([^\"]*)")
public TestRecordHelper runDriverCommand(java.lang.String command)
                                                                           throws java.lang.Throwable
        Run a SAFS Driver Command. The safs command takes no parameters. This method performs SAFS Expression processing on all input parameters.

        Regexen: "do safs command ([^\"]*)"

        Example Scenario Step:

          Then do safs command ClearClipboard
        Parameters:
        command - The DriverCommand keyword (command) to perform
        Throws:
        java.lang.Throwable

      • runDriverCommand

        @Then(value="do safs command ([^\"]*) using \"(.+)\"")
public TestRecordHelper runDriverCommand(java.lang.String command,
                                                                                                 java.util.List<java.lang.String> parameters)
                                                                                          throws java.lang.Throwable
        Run a SAFS Driver Command. The safs command may take one or more parameters. This method performs SAFS Expression processing on all input parameters.

        Regexen: "do safs command ([^\"]*) using \"(.+)\"

        Example Scenario Step:

          Then do safs command GetAppMapValue using " , ApplicationConstants, WebURL, varURL"
        Parameters:
        command - The DriverCommand keyword (command) to perform
        parameters - List<String> of parameters used by the command. Can be null.
        Throws:
        java.lang.Throwable

      • runComponentFunction

        @Then(value="do safs action ([^\"]*) on ([^\"]*)")
public TestRecordHelper runComponentFunction(java.lang.String command,
                                                                                                 java.lang.String parent)
                                                                                          throws java.lang.Throwable
        Run a SAFS Component Function on a top-level component (Window). The particular safs action takes no additional parameters. This method performs SAFS Expression processing on all input parameters.

        Regexen: "do safs action ([^\"]*) on ([^\"]*)"

        Example Scenario Step:

          Then do safs action GuiDoesExist on LoginWindow
        Parameters:
        command - The ComponentFunction keyword (action) to perform
        parent - The ComponentFunction parent window name to act on
        Returns:
        Throws:
        java.lang.Throwable
